FYI, the murmur64 for Long is actually pretty trivial.

{code}
  public static long hash64(long data) {
    long hash = DEFAULT_SEED;
    long k = Long.reverseBytes(data);
    int length = Long.BYTES;
    // mix functions
    k *= C1;
    k = Long.rotateLeft(k, R1);
    k *= C2;
    hash ^= k;
    hash = Long.rotateLeft(hash, R2) * M + N1;
    // finalization
    hash ^= length;
    hash = fmix64(hash);

    return hash;
  }
{code}

and does not need a byte[] array.

The short and int versions are nearly identical, except they need to account for the sign-bit during the cast up from int -> long by doing 

{code}
  public static long hash64(int data) {
    long k1 = Integer.reverseBytes(data) & (-1L >>> 32);
    int length = Integer.BYTES;
    long hash = DEFAULT_SEED;
    k1 *= C1;
    k1 = Long.rotateLeft(k1, R1);
    k1 *= C2;
    hash ^= k1;
    // finalization
    hash ^= length;
    hash = fmix64(hash);
    return hash;
  }
{code}
